http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Held-on-charge-of-molesting-minor/article14020677.ece

A 65-year-old man, identified as Mohanan of Kesavadasapuram, was arrested on Sunday on charges of sexually harassing an 11-year-old girl.The Peroorkada police said the accused had allegedly harassed and molested the girl in a by-lane in Kesavadasapuram on Thursday, as she was returning home after tuitions around 4.30 p.m. The child had to be given medical care at the SAT Hospital. She lodged her complaint with the police on Sunday, following which Mohanan was arrested.The police said the accused was involved in similar crimes earlier as well. An unsolved crime, registered after a complaint lodged by a minor girl from Pattom, was solved after Mohanan reportedly confessed to that crime as well. It had remained unsolved after the complainant failed to identify the accused from several suspects rounded up by the police.He was produced in court and remanded in judicial custody on Monday.